Raw Job Description:
The Global Energy Infrastructure Solutions (GEIS) group is part of the wider Eaton Electrical Group and contains the Crouse Hinds division which manufactures high grade electrical products for hazardous, industrial, and commercial applications world-wide. We are looking for a Supply Chain Analyst to ensure the timely supply of products within GEIS portfolio. The successful candidate will work with product managers and suppliers to achieve inventory and customer service goals.

We are an engineering-to-order-come business, and if you are looking to get stuck into a complex challenge that not only allows you but actively encourages you to look at better ways of working, this could be your role.

Key Duties

- Manage the inbound supply of materials for a nominated portfolio.
- Create, review, and execute purchasing plans within budgets and targets.
- Review open POs for potential changes and also new PO recommendations that will keep the plan moving.
- Build and maintain stakeholder relationships with focus on accurate communication.
- Analyse purchasing processes to eliminate negative impacts through continuous improvement.
- Implement the most efficient cost-to-serve model using existing organisational knowledge.
- Working with the Supply Chain and Logistics teams to optimise stock flow, resolving capacity, costs, and availability conflicts.
- Manage vendor communication and negotiation to ensure alignment on delivery schedules, pricing, and service expectations.

Qualifications

- Minimum of 2 years of experience as a supply chain or logistics analysts preferably for a manufacturing firm in any industry (for e.g. electrical, mechanical, healthcare, FMCG).
- Knowledge of supply chain concepts, including how safety stock levels can be influenced.
- Intermediate Excel skills with experience in SAP. 
- Tertiary qualifications in supply chain, business, or engineering.
- Self-motivated, team player, willing to learn, problem solver.

What We Offer

- Competitive salary with access to bonus scheme
- Inclusive working environment
- Volunteer days
- Outstanding training and development programs for both professional and personal development

Do you have a desire to make a positive impact on the climate and biodiversity crises by working with an innovative global think tank? If so, we want to hear from you!

InfluenceMap is best known for its LobbyMap platform, which analyzes corporate advocacy and policy engagement activities related to climate change and biodiversity loss. Our work has been featured in the media globally, used by hundreds of investors, and informed numerous climate campaigns. Other work streams include the FinanceMap platform, which assesses the climate credentials of the financial sector, and the Carbon Majors platform, which tracks emissions from the world's largest polluters. With offices in London, New York, Tokyo, Seoul, Canberra, and Brussels, this is an opportunity to be part of a team of 70+ friendly and dynamic professionals and to help shape our culture as we continue to grow and evolve as an organization. You will also have the chance to work with our global network of partners to help develop and share our cutting-edge content.

We are seeking an Analyst to join our team who will be responsible for assessing companies on their climate change and/or biodiversity loss policies. This is an entry-level analyst position that is likely to suit someone starting their career. You will be working on the LobbyMap workstream. By mastering our methodology and processes, you will have the opportunity to specialize in corporate climate policy engagement in China.

Full training in our research methods and how to effectively communicate our results will be provided. Upon demonstrating your ability in this specialization, you may also have the opportunity to develop expertise in other areas, such as specific sectors, policy areas, or geographic regions, in line with the organization's project needs. Our approach is highly data-driven and emphasizes accuracy, consistency, and meticulous attention to detail. InfluenceMap's work is in widespread use by finance, the media, and other stakeholders; thus, we place great importance on the ability to communicate our content (both written and verbal) effectively.

Requirements

- Fluency in English (written and spoken) 
- Outstanding analytical and data analysis skills, with a very strong attention to detail 
- Ability to communicate complex issues and data-driven analysis convincingly
- IT and software skills across a range of standard applications
- Right to work in Japan or Australia. 

We are an enthusiastic, highly motivated, mission-aligned team. We are seeking a candidate with a similar outlook.

Benefits

The Revenue & Trade Management Analyst role is pivotal in enabling data-driven decision-making across commercial operations. This position is responsible for delivering accurate and timely reporting, supporting strategic revenue initiatives, and ensuring effective governance of trade investments. Key responsibilities include maintaining and enhancing sales dashboards, analyzing promotional performance and ROI, and supporting customer planning through validation of claims and promotional strategies. Additionally, the role contributes to global reporting, supports audit requirements, tracks key supply chain metrics, and reconciles commercial budgets.

Main Responsibilities:

- Maintain and refresh sales dashboards and weekly reports on time
- Ensure data accuracy by validating key deviations and identifying/reporting any errors promptly
- Publish reports in a timely manner to enable informed commercial decisions
- Provide timely promotion and event ROI analysis to support trade spend effectiveness
- Deliver actionable promotional insights to assist the Strategic Revenue Management (SRM) Manager in executing the agenda
- Ensure consistent tracking of performance against promotional objectives
- Execute claim approvals in a timely manner, adhering to the Customer Commitment Framework
- Perform proof of performance and customer commitment checks to support trade compliance
- Monitor promotional strategy governance and escalate non-compliance where necessary
- Accurately submit 3NP, RTM, CSU data, and international customer templates within deadlines
- Ensure high-quality reporting with no data errors, meeting external stakeholder expectations
- Analyze submitted data for consistency, accuracy, and completeness
- Support internal and end-of-year audit processes by maintaining accurate documentation across reporting, claims, and budget records
- Proactively identify and resolve audit risks in collaboration with cross-functional teams to ensure compliance and readiness
- Monitor and report Sell-In vs Sell-Out volumes (IRI data), escalating discrepancies to ensure alignment between commercial and supply teams
- Provide timely and accurate volume tracking to support demand planning and Sales & Operations Planning (S&OP) processes
- Reconcile commercial budgets to ensure alignment with national sales targets and financial objectives
- Support the Revenue & Trade Management Manager in tracking budget performance across key accounts and identifying opportunities for trade spend optimization

Who we are looking for:

- University degree in Business, Finance, or a related field
- Previous experience in a similar role, ideally within FMCG industry
- Strong data analysis and insight oriented reporting skills, with ability to identify trends and anomalies in data
- Strong time management and prioritization skills

- Proficiency in Excel and handling large datasets
- Familiarity with business processes and promotional strategy governance is a plus
- Good communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with multiple stakeholders

Our Culture

In return, you will be presented with opportunities to develop your career and collaborate with talented colleagues in a supportive, diverse environment.

At Cognizant we recognize that companies that are open and welcoming to a multi-culturally diverse workforce will thrive with fresh perspectives and collaborative knowledge. Cognizant focuses on promoting & increasing gender diversity and providing a workplace which encourages great participation and an equal playing field, where merit and accomplishment are the only criteria for success.

Position Summary

The Robotic Process Automation (RPA) Business Process Analyst will excel in RPA (Power automate), presenting both consulting and development skillsets. They will work closely with business stakeholders through completing consulting led RPA process assessments, documenting business processes, communicating to development teams on requirements and having experience in agile RPA delivery. They will collaborate with a client to enable them to deliver and scale RPA solutions. They will play a critical role in the growth of the Cognizant team and its RPA capability across ANZ. One key part of the role will be to identify quality and prioritising opportunities to automate process, demonstrating to clients the achievement of benefits and suggesting process improvements as part of a continuous journey.

Roles And Responsibilities

- RPA Tool understanding. (Uipath, Power Automate desktop, Blue Prism)
- Collaborating with stakeholders to understand “as-is” process, issues, areas for improvement, leveraging system data to confirm conclusions where necessary.
- Document business processes using Process Definition Documents (PDD), Standard Operating Procedures.
- Responsible for documenting business process flow charts using BPMN principles.
- Design clear and understandable “to=be” processes, replay them to the business and get sign off for them to be developed and implemented.
- Work with change management teams to ensure the early adoption of new processes.
- Working on Support and Maintenance activities
- Experience managing daily stand ups, retrospectives leveraging agile methodologies (Scrum).
- Project management: disciplined in managing project scope, timeline, and budget to meet deadlines.
- Work within project schedule constraints, communicating any identified project risks and issues.
- Create Handover Documentation
- Write test cases against the desired requirements.
- Review UAT test plans, run UAT triage and clarification/manage defects.
- Test and confirm the desired requirement has been met considering original ROI.

Mandatory Skills

- Strong analytical and strategic thinking.
- A proactive approach to identifying opportunities and driving solutions independently. 
- Able to understand complex processes and simplify where possible, or break down into sub-processes, ability to identify redundancy.
- Able to determine ROI of processes and create business pipeline. Work with the business to identify best cases for automation.
- Possess expert communication and facilitation.
- Working effectively with people at all levels of the organization to understand needs and deploy solutions. 
- Familiarity with digital tools and the ability to use statistical models and data to simulate and predict the impact of changes. 
- Thoroughness and a focus on detail are important for creating accurate and effective architectural designs. 
- The ability to navigate organizational politics and build consensus among different stakeholders. 
- Capable of playing a lead role and communicating requirements to both onshore and offshore teams.
- Ability to playback future “to-be” solutions to multiple audiences with varying degrees of technological maturity.
- Familiarisation with JIRA, Confluence tools
- Familiarity with Microsoft power automate.
- Possess excellent communication skills.
- Enthusiastic and unprompted attitude for implementing and developing fresh solutions.
- Knowledge of BPM, RPA, and AI API’s
- Initiative-taker: self-directed and initiative-taking in managing tasks and setting challenging targets to achieve client’s demands.

Next Steps

Overview

The Graduate Research Analyst is a pivotal role within Canstar’s Research Department, tailored for graduates eager to delve into the financial services industry. Reporting to the Ratings Manager, this role focuses on contributing to the development and delivery of Canstar’s renowned star ratings and industry awards. This position requires strong analytical skills, adaptability, and collaboration, offering a solid foundation for building knowledge in financial products, market analytics, and consumer trends.

Key Responsibilities

Star Ratings and Awards Management

- Assist in the design and implementation of Canstar’s Star Ratings and Awards, applying robust methodologies and maintaining consistency with industry standards.
- Manage star rating projects and other research tasks, ensuring timely and quality delivery.
- Implement quality assurance processes to ensure accuracy and comparability in ratings and calculations.
- Participate in research projects on behalf of financial institutions, government departments, and other related organisations.
- Support client engagement by discussing market developments, responding to rating results, and providing research insights.

General Duties

- Develop and maintain an understanding of consumer behaviour, product features, pricing trends, and regulatory issues such as disclosure and competition.
- Document procedures and maintain resources to support recurring and ad hoc research requests.
- Proactively identify opportunities to improve processes, methodologies, and efficiencies in ratings and awards delivery.
- Contribute to cross-functional projects by supplying analysis, insights, and solutions to other teams across the business.

Communication

- Liaise with both technical and non-technical stakeholders, translating complex concepts into clear, actionable insights.
- Collaborate with Editorial, Media, Product, and other teams to ensure alignment and effective communication of research outcomes.
- Participate in internal discussions and presentations relating to methodology, market trends, and award results.

Other Duties

- Remain open to taking on additional responsibilities or adapting to changes in job requirements.
- Engage in ongoing professional development and learning opportunities in the finance and research sectors.

- Tackle diverse and challenging projects that directly influence business strategy and customer outcomes.
- Collaborate with a supportive, forward-thinking team that thrives on innovation.

Job Description

About the role:

You’ll collaborate with project teams, business analysts and engineers to understand and document business requirements. Your role will collaborate with the People First Bank business areas to assist with the deployment of Power BI within the organisation.

This role is offered as a 12 months fixed term contract with potential extension or permanency.

Key Responsibilities

-  Work with stakeholders to elicit, analyse, communicate and validate analytics and reporting requirements for Power BI. 
-  Facilitate workshops with business analysts to document business processes and requirements. 
-  Develop functional specifications for engineers. 
-  Assist in the development of Power BI semantic layer. 
-  Support the development and testing phases of data projects. 
-  Guide the business through the adoption of Power BI best practices. 
-  Design, build and development dashboards to meet business needs / requirements, ensuring that business needs are met. 

About You

You are outcomes focussed, have a curious mind-set and work collaboratively with the team and the business to support Power BI rollout.

Knowledge And Experience

-  Strong knowledge of SQL, data modelling and DAX. 
-  Proven experience in eliciting requirements and developing functional specifications. 
-  An understanding of financial services operating environment and products (desirable). 
-  Knowledge of DataBricks, C# scripting 
-  Extensive experience in enterprise Power BI environment. 

Why You’ll Love Working With Us

People First Bank – our new brand – says exactly what we’re all about: people. We're committed to supporting and growing our team and creating an outstanding work environment.

You’ll have access to financial and lifestyle benefits to support your success and individuality:

-  Flexibility and hybrid working arrangements. 
-  Enhance your salary with discounts on banking, health insurance, and shopping across Australia. 
-  Advance your career with training, study support, and project opportunities. 
-  Competitive leave benefits that empower employees to take time for themselves and loved ones. 
-  Wellbeing support with our Employee Assistance Program, wellbeing leave, mental health app, and mental health ambassadors’ program . 
-  Make a difference with paid volunteering, Workplace Giving, and diverse community initiatives. 
-  Be recognised for your contributions through our peer-driven recognition program. 

A bit about People First Bank:

In March 2023, People’s Choice and Heritage Bank merged to form Heritage and People’s Choice Limited - Australia's leading mutual bank. We are now on an exciting journey to bring together our products, services, and technology under a single brand - People First Bank.

We have over 700,000 members and 1,900 employees, with dual head offices in Adelaide and Toowoomba, an Australian-based contract centre and branches across five states.

With a vision ‘To deliver positive change through banking’, People First Bank serves members and contributes to the community, while offering an inclusive, flexible work environment. We’re big enough to make an impact; but agile enough to influence and do interesting work.

Position Overview

This role provides innovative solutions, maintenance and support to Council's Business Technology ERP systems including TechnologyOne's Software as a Service (SaaS).

The Systems Support Analyst is an integral part of Shellharbour City Councils Information Technology team which is a vibrant, dynamic and high performing group of professionals who continually aim to deliver customer first and customer focused technology outcomes.

Located in a state-of-the-art office building in the Shellharbour City Centre that provides access to exceptional facilities and a modern progressive office environment which promotes Collaboration and Innovation. The role provides the right person the opportunity to work with the latest and most modern technology and systems assisting in delivering innovative solutions to internal and external customers in a vibrant and dynamic technology environment.

Key Responsibilities

- Maintain corporate systems across Council, including Property and Rating (P&R), Financial, Enterprise Asset Management (EAM), Customer Request Management (CRM) and Electronic Document Management System (EDMS).
- Provide Level 1/2 troubleshooting support, resolving issues and offering workarounds to mitigate future incidents.
- Implement and maintain updates, patches and service packs to ensure software environments are supported effectively.
- Develop professional relationships with key stakeholders, including IT staff and third-party vendors.
- Identify opportunities to enhance business processes and workflows, contributing to overall efficiency.
- Assist with IT projects by managing planning, meetings, communication and reporting.
- Conduct training sessions and create materials to support the implementation of new business processes and information systems.
- Promote the adoption of new technologies and continuous improvement practices.

Candidate Profile

The ideal candidate will possess a strong background in Information Technology, complemented by relevant experience in software systems administration and customer service. You will have demonstrated skills in problem-solving, analytical thinking and effective communication.

- Degree in Information Technology or relevant accreditation.
- Experience in supporting and administering software systems within a large organisation.
- Proven ability to lead initiatives that enhance customer experience and drive business improvements.
- Strong interpersonal skills with a focus on collaboration and stakeholder engagement.

Knowledge of Local Government operations and familiarity with TechnologyOne One Council solutions will be advantageous. You should be proactive in seeking feedback and committed to continuous personal and professional development.

Salary & Benefits

The salary for this position ranges from $84,649 to $89,830, reflecting the skills and experience of the successful candidate. In addition to a supportive work environment, we offer a comprehensive benefits package that includes:

- Flexible working arrangements to promote work-life balance.
- Professional development opportunities to enhance your skills and career progression.

The Opportunity

Ventia’s Group Supply Chain team is excited to introduce a newly created Data Analyst role. This position is ideal for someone with strong experience in supply chain, operations, or procurement. In this role, you’ll work closely with our Data Engineer to harness data and drive impactful improvements across supply chain operations. Your insights will help identify efficiencies and enhance performance within the Group Supply Chain. Acting as a vital bridge between raw data and strategic decision-making, you’ll ensure business outcomes are guided by robust, data-driven analysis.

What’s in it for you?

- Flexible work arrangements to support work-life balance
- Work alongside a supportive, experienced, and collaborative team
- Access to cross-disciplinary learning opportunities across Ventia’s diverse sectors
- Ongoing training and professional development to support your career growth
- A range of fantastic Ventia employee benefits, including discounted private health insurance, paid parental leave, discounted travel, and more!

Key Accountabilities

- Data Analysis & Insights: Analyse complex supply chain datasets (inventory, logistics, procurement, demand planning) using Databricks to uncover trends, anomalies, and opportunities for optimisation. Conduct root-cause analysis on key metrics to drive performance improvements.
- Data Engineering & ETL: Build and maintain SQL/Python scripts in Databricks for efficient ETL processes, ensuring high data quality and accessibility.
- Reporting & Visualisation: Develop interactive dashboards and reports using Power BI or Tableau to provide real-time visibility and support data-driven decisions.
- Stakeholder Engagement: Collaborate with logistics, operations, and procurement teams to understand business needs, translate them into analytical solutions, and deliver actionable insights.
- Continuous Improvement & Governance: Enhance data processes and reporting frameworks while ensuring data integrity in partnership with engineering teams.

About You

- Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Statistics, Operations Research, Supply Chain Management, or a related field.
- Solid professional experience in data analysis or business intelligence, within supply chain, logistics, or operations.
- Advanced SQL skills for data querying and manipulation.
- Hands-on experience with Databricks, including Lakehouse architecture and notebooks.
- Proficient in Python for large-scale data analysis and scripting.
- Skilled in creating interactive dashboards using Power BI or Tableau.
- Strong understanding of ETL processes and data warehousing.
- Familiarity with supply chain data models and metrics (e.g., inventory turnover, lead time, forecast accuracy).
- Excellent communication skills with the ability to translate complex data into clear business insights.
- Strong analytical and problem-solving capabilities.
- Self-motivated and collaborative team player.

Ventia is a leading infrastructure services company, operating across Australia and New Zealand. Our clients are the owners and operators of assets that are critical to our local communities. We pride ourselves on working smart, safely and sustainably, harnessing the latest technologies and brightest minds. About the Role:

The Revenue & Trade Management Analyst role is pivotal in enabling data-driven decision-making across commercial operations. This position is responsible for delivering accurate and timely reporting, supporting strategic revenue initiatives, and ensuring effective governance of trade investments. Key responsibilities include maintaining and enhancing sales dashboards, analyzing promotional performance and ROI, and supporting customer planning through validation of claims and promotional strategies. Additionally, the role contributes to global reporting, supports audit requirements, tracks key supply chain metrics, and reconciles commercial budgets.

Main Responsibilities:

- Maintain and refresh sales dashboards and weekly reports on time
- Ensure data accuracy by validating key deviations and identifying/reporting any errors promptly
- Publish reports in a timely manner to enable informed commercial decisions
- Provide timely promotion and event ROI analysis to support trade spend effectiveness
- Deliver actionable promotional insights to assist the Strategic Revenue Management (SRM) Manager in executing the agenda
- Ensure consistent tracking of performance against promotional objectives
- Execute claim approvals in a timely manner, adhering to the Customer Commitment Framework
- Perform proof of performance and customer commitment checks to support trade compliance
- Monitor promotional strategy governance and escalate non-compliance where necessary
- Accurately submit 3NP, RTM, CSU data, and international customer templates within deadlines
- Ensure high-quality reporting with no data errors, meeting external stakeholder expectations
- Analyze submitted data for consistency, accuracy, and completeness
- Support internal and end-of-year audit processes by maintaining accurate documentation across reporting, claims, and budget records
- Proactively identify and resolve audit risks in collaboration with cross-functional teams to ensure compliance and readiness
- Monitor and report Sell-In vs Sell-Out volumes (IRI data), escalating discrepancies to ensure alignment between commercial and supply teams
- Provide timely and accurate volume tracking to support demand planning and Sales & Operations Planning (S&OP) processes
- Reconcile commercial budgets to ensure alignment with national sales targets and financial objectives
- Support the Revenue & Trade Management Manager in tracking budget performance across key accounts and identifying opportunities for trade spend optimization

Who we are looking for:

- University degree in Business, Finance, or a related field
- Previous experience in a similar role, ideally within FMCG industry
- Strong data analysis and insight oriented reporting skills, with ability to identify trends and anomalies in data
- Strong time management and prioritization skills
- Results-orientation with a willingness to learn
- Proficiency in Excel and handling large datasets
- Familiarity with business processes and promotional strategy governance is a plus
- Good communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with multiple stakeholders

At Emergent Consulting, we partner with organisations across healthcare, education, construction, and beyond to deliver business and technology transformation. Our consultants don’t just advise — they roll up their sleeves and make change happen. We are looking for a motivated consultant with strong business analysis and delivery expertise to join our growing team. This permanent role offers the chance to work directly with clients, contribute across the full project lifecycle, and grow within a consultancy that values excellence, collaboration, and impact.
The RoleAs a Consultant, you will play a hands-on role in both shaping and delivering solutions. You will:
- Analyse & Advise – Work with stakeholders to define requirements, assess processes, and design fit-for-purpose business and technology solutions.
- Implement & Deliver – Support end-to-end project implementation, including system configuration support, data migration, testing, training needs analysis, and transition planning.
- Improve & Transform – Drive business process improvements, design new client journeys, and contribute to change management planning and execution.
- Engage Clients – Build trusted relationships, provide clear reporting, and support project tracking across budgets, risks, and issues.
- Collaborate & Grow – Partner with senior consultants on diverse projects, ensuring deliverables meet the highest standards while developing your consulting career.
About YouWe’re looking for consultants who are highly qualified and thrive in both analysis and delivery:
- Tertiary degree in Information Technology, Information Systems, Business, or a related field (essential).
- Proven experience in business analysis and project delivery in complex environments.
- Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills.
- A proactive, adaptable mindset — equally comfortable advising and rolling up your sleeves.
- Professional certifications in Business Analysis, Project Management, or Change Management (advantageous but not essential).
Why Emergent?At Emergent, you’ll find more than a role — you’ll find a consulting career:
- Full Lifecycle Consulting – Work from problem definition through to implementation.
- Career Growth – Learn from senior consultants and progress into leadership roles.
- Diverse Projects – Gain exposure across industries and technologies.
- Direct Client Impact – See your analysis translated into real-world outcomes.
- Collaborative Culture – Be part of a supportive, empowered consulting team.
How to Apply?Applying for our job is easy — Apply directly via LinkedIn.
Right to Work in Australia
- While all applications will be acknowledged, only candidates with the right to work in Australia through citizenship or holding an appropriate Visa can be considered. If you are not an Australian citizen, please provide clear evidence of your current visa status in your application.
Remote Work with Some Travel Required
- While the position is remote, Emergent operates within business hours relevant to Eastern and Central states in Australia. The successful candidate must be based in an Eastern and Central Australian state.
Join Emergent Consulting and be part of a team that designs, implements, and delivers consulting solutions that matter.

Cognizant (NASDAQ: CTSH) is a leading provider of information technology, consulting, and business process services, dedicated to helping the world's leading companies build stronger businesses. Headquartered in Teaneck, New Jersey (U.S.), Cognizant combines a passion for client satisfaction, technology innovation, deep industry and business process expertise, and a global, collaborative workforce that embodies the future of work. Cognizant is a member of the NASDAQ-100, the S&P 500, the Forbes Global 2000, and the Fortune 500 and is ranked among the top performing and fastest growing companies in the world.

Our Culture

Your passion, integrity and experience are integral to Cognizant's success. You will join into a dynamic and expanding global leader in IT and Business consultancy where you will be valued for who you are. We take pride in our partnership with our clients, so your ability to add value and provide exceptional service to our clients is fundamental to your success. In return, you will be presented with opportunities to develop your career and collaborate with talented colleagues in a supportive, diverse environment.

At Cognizant we recognize that companies that are open and welcoming to a multi-culturally diverse workforce will thrive with fresh perspectives and collaborative knowledge. Cognizant focuses on promoting & increasing gender diversity and providing a workplace which encourages great participation and an equal playing field, where merit and accomplishment are the only criteria for success.

Position Summary

The Robotic Process Automation (RPA) Business Process Analyst will excel in RPA (Power automate), presenting both consulting and development skillsets. They will work closely with business stakeholders through completing consulting led RPA process assessments, documenting business processes, communicating to development teams on requirements and having experience in agile RPA delivery. They will collaborate with a client to enable them to deliver and scale RPA solutions. They will play a critical role in the growth of the Cognizant team and its RPA capability across ANZ. One key part of the role will be to identify quality and prioritising opportunities to automate process, demonstrating to clients the achievement of benefits and suggesting process improvements as part of a continuous journey.

Roles And Responsibilities

- RPA Tool understanding. (Uipath, Power Automate desktop, Blue Prism)
- Collaborating with stakeholders to understand “as-is” process, issues, areas for improvement, leveraging system data to confirm conclusions where necessary.
- Document business processes using Process Definition Documents (PDD), Standard Operating Procedures.
- Responsible for documenting business process flow charts using BPMN principles.
- Design clear and understandable “to=be” processes, replay them to the business and get sign off for them to be developed and implemented.
- Work with change management teams to ensure the early adoption of new processes.
- Working on Support and Maintenance activities
- Experience managing daily stand ups, retrospectives leveraging agile methodologies (Scrum).
- Project management: disciplined in managing project scope, timeline, and budget to meet deadlines.
- Work within project schedule constraints, communicating any identified project risks and issues.
- Create Handover Documentation
- Write test cases against the desired requirements.
- Review UAT test plans, run UAT triage and clarification/manage defects.
- Test and confirm the desired requirement has been met considering original ROI.

Mandatory Skills

- Strong analytical and strategic thinking.
- A proactive approach to identifying opportunities and driving solutions independently. 
- Able to understand complex processes and simplify where possible, or break down into sub-processes, ability to identify redundancy.
- Able to determine ROI of processes and create business pipeline. Work with the business to identify best cases for automation.
- Possess expert communication and facilitation.
- Working effectively with people at all levels of the organization to understand needs and deploy solutions. 
- Familiarity with digital tools and the ability to use statistical models and data to simulate and predict the impact of changes. 
- Thoroughness and a focus on detail are important for creating accurate and effective architectural designs. 
- The ability to navigate organizational politics and build consensus among different stakeholders. 
- Capable of playing a lead role and communicating requirements to both onshore and offshore teams.
- Ability to playback future “to-be” solutions to multiple audiences with varying degrees of technological maturity.
- Familiarisation with JIRA, Confluence tools
- Familiarity with Microsoft power automate.
- Possess excellent communication skills.
- Enthusiastic and unprompted attitude for implementing and developing fresh solutions.
- Knowledge of BPM, RPA, and AI API’s
- Initiative-taker: self-directed and initiative-taking in managing tasks and setting challenging targets to achieve client’s demands.

Next Steps

If you feel this opportunity suits you, or Cognizant is the type of organization you would like to join, we want to have a conversation with you! Please apply directly with us.

For a complete list of open opportunities with Cognizant, visit http://www.cognizant.com/careers. Cognizant is committed to providing Equal Employment Opportunities. Successful candidates will be required to undergo a background check.

Power up your career as a Systems Support Analyst

- Join a dynamic team dedicated to optimising software solutions for enhanced customer experience.
- Utilise your IT expertise to drive innovation and business improvement.

About Shellharbour City Council

Shellharbour City Council is committed to delivering high-quality services to our community while fostering a sustainable environment. Our team strives for excellence and continuously seeks innovative solutions to meet the needs of our residents and stakeholders.

We embrace a culture of collaboration and accountability, ensuring that every team member contributes to our goals. As part of our commitment to inclusivity, we celebrate the diversity of our community and empower our employees to reach their full potential.

Position Overview

This role provides innovative solutions, maintenance and support to Council's Business Technology ERP systems including TechnologyOne's Software as a Service (SaaS).

The Systems Support Analyst is an integral part of Shellharbour City Councils Information Technology team which is a vibrant, dynamic and high performing group of professionals who continually aim to deliver customer first and customer focused technology outcomes.

Located in a state-of-the-art office building in the Shellharbour City Centre that provides access to exceptional facilities and a modern progressive office environment which promotes Collaboration and Innovation. The role provides the right person the opportunity to work with the latest and most modern technology and systems assisting in delivering innovative solutions to internal and external customers in a vibrant and dynamic technology environment.

Key Responsibilities

- Maintain corporate systems across Council, including Property and Rating (P&R), Financial, Enterprise Asset Management (EAM), Customer Request Management (CRM) and Electronic Document Management System (EDMS).
- Provide Level 1/2 troubleshooting support, resolving issues and offering workarounds to mitigate future incidents.
- Implement and maintain updates, patches and service packs to ensure software environments are supported effectively.
- Develop professional relationships with key stakeholders, including IT staff and third-party vendors.
- Identify opportunities to enhance business processes and workflows, contributing to overall efficiency.
- Assist with IT projects by managing planning, meetings, communication and reporting.
- Conduct training sessions and create materials to support the implementation of new business processes and information systems.
- Promote the adoption of new technologies and continuous improvement practices.

Candidate Profile

The ideal candidate will possess a strong background in Information Technology, complemented by relevant experience in software systems administration and customer service. You will have demonstrated skills in problem-solving, analytical thinking and effective communication.

- Degree in Information Technology or relevant accreditation.
- Experience in supporting and administering software systems within a large organisation.
- Proven ability to lead initiatives that enhance customer experience and drive business improvements.
- Strong interpersonal skills with a focus on collaboration and stakeholder engagement.

Knowledge of Local Government operations and familiarity with TechnologyOne One Council solutions will be advantageous. You should be proactive in seeking feedback and committed to continuous personal and professional development.

Salary & Benefits

The salary for this position ranges from $84,649 to $89,830, reflecting the skills and experience of the successful candidate. In addition to a supportive work environment, we offer a comprehensive benefits package that includes:

- Flexible working arrangements to promote work-life balance.
- Professional development opportunities to enhance your skills and career progression.
- Health and wellness programs to support your well-being.
- Employee recognition initiatives to celebrate your contributions.

If you are passionate about leveraging technology to improve services and enhance customer experiences, we encourage you to apply for the Systems Support Analyst position at Shellharbour City Council.

ASIC is seeking an Analyst – Business Engagement & Enquiries to join the Digital Team. This role has a strong customer service focus combined with general troubleshooting skills and acts as a liaison point between business units, project teams, and IT to resolve customer issues.

- Sydney, Melbourne or Perth. Open to other locations
- $81,396 - $85,659 (depending on experience) + 15.4% superannuation
- 12-month Fixed Term Contract position
- Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, Thursday 9 October 2025  

The team 

The Digital team supports business systems and processes that build excellence in regulatory operations.

The team provides the user-centred design service and manages the ongoing development of the key platform underpinning the regulatory workflows across ASIC – the ASIC CRM, ASIC Regulatory Portal, ASIC Search and related data and document repositories, as well as ASIC's key externally facing digital channels such as the corporate website.

The role

The purpose of the Analyst within the Digital team is to manage enquiries related to OneASIC Regulatory systems, providing expert troubleshooting support.

Responsibilities Will Include

- Act as liaison between business units, project teams, and IT to resolve customer issues
- Efficiently resolve or escalate issues with strong verbal communication
- Document technical issues and solutions clearly
- Manage external stakeholder interactions via the ASIC Regulatory Portal
- Support stakeholder training and update learning materials
- Drive process improvement and innovation
- Assist with system enhancements, new products, and releases
- Create clear, user-friendly release communications for non-technical audiences
- Build and maintain relationships with subject matter experts and stakeholders

About You

A successful applicant should possess many or all of the following: 

- Relevant degree or experience in customer and stakeholder engagement
- Strong stakeholder management and influencing skills
- Excellent communication and issue resolution abilities
- Skilled in multitasking and prioritising in fast-paced settings
- Understanding of business processes and user reviews
- Experience analysing database information and providing solutions
- Effective problem-solving and issue triage skills
- Team-oriented with strong collaboration experience
- Proficient in Microsoft Dynamics CRM, SharePoint, and similar systems
- Strong customer service and issue resolution skills
- Efficient task management with timely, quality outcomes

The Opportunity

Ventia’s Group Supply Chain team is excited to introduce a newly created Data Analyst role. This position is ideal for someone with strong experience in supply chain, operations, or procurement. In this role, you’ll work closely with our Data Engineer to harness data and drive impactful improvements across supply chain operations. Your insights will help identify efficiencies and enhance performance within the Group Supply Chain. Acting as a vital bridge between raw data and strategic decision-making, you’ll ensure business outcomes are guided by robust, data-driven analysis.

What’s in it for you?

- Flexible work arrangements to support work-life balance
- Work alongside a supportive, experienced, and collaborative team
- Access to cross-disciplinary learning opportunities across Ventia’s diverse sectors
- Ongoing training and professional development to support your career growth
- A range of fantastic Ventia employee benefits, including discounted private health insurance, paid parental leave, discounted travel, and more!

Key Accountabilities

- Data Analysis & Insights: Analyse complex supply chain datasets (inventory, logistics, procurement, demand planning) using Databricks to uncover trends, anomalies, and opportunities for optimisation. Conduct root-cause analysis on key metrics to drive performance improvements.
- Data Engineering & ETL: Build and maintain SQL/Python scripts in Databricks for efficient ETL processes, ensuring high data quality and accessibility.
- Reporting & Visualisation: Develop interactive dashboards and reports using Power BI or Tableau to provide real-time visibility and support data-driven decisions.
- Stakeholder Engagement: Collaborate with logistics, operations, and procurement teams to understand business needs, translate them into analytical solutions, and deliver actionable insights.
- Continuous Improvement & Governance: Enhance data processes and reporting frameworks while ensuring data integrity in partnership with engineering teams.

About You

- Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Statistics, Operations Research, Supply Chain Management, or a related field.
- Solid professional experience in data analysis or business intelligence, within supply chain, logistics, or operations.
- Advanced SQL skills for data querying and manipulation.
- Hands-on experience with Databricks, including Lakehouse architecture and notebooks.
- Proficient in Python for large-scale data analysis and scripting.
- Skilled in creating interactive dashboards using Power BI or Tableau.
- Strong understanding of ETL processes and data warehousing.
- Familiarity with supply chain data models and metrics (e.g., inventory turnover, lead time, forecast accuracy).
- Excellent communication skills with the ability to translate complex data into clear business insights.
- Strong analytical and problem-solving capabilities.
- Self-motivated and collaborative team player.

About Ventia

Ventia is a leading infrastructure services company, operating across Australia and New Zealand. Our clients are the owners and operators of assets that are critical to our local communities. We pride ourselves on working smart, safely and sustainably, harnessing the latest technologies and brightest minds. With a diverse and proud heritage, we have a track record of delivering essential services to the communities in which we operate.

Diversity 

Ventia is enriched by the diverse experiences, talents and cultures that our people bring to the organisation, while celebrating and respecting the communities we operate in. We are committed to providing a safe and positive environment that provides equal opportunities for individuals of all backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, LGBTQIA+, Women, Veterans and spouses and people with disabilities.

At Mindrift, innovation meets opportunity. We believe in using the power of collective human intelligence to ethically shape the future of AI.

The Mindrift platform, launched and powered by Toloka, connects domain experts with cutting-edge AI projects from innovative tech clients. Our mission is to unlock the potential of GenAI by tapping into real-world expertise from across the globe.

Who we're looking for:

We're looking for curious and intellectually proactive contributors, the kind of person who double-checks assumptions and plays devil's advocate.

Are you comfortable with ambiguity and complexity? Does an async, remote, flexible opportunity sound exciting? Would you like to learn how modern AI systems are tested and evaluated?

This is a flexible, project-based opportunity well-suited for:

- Analysts, researchers, or consultants with strong critical thinking skills
- Students (senior undergrads / grad students) looking for an intellectually interesting gig
- People open to a part-time and non-permanent opportunity

About the project:

We're on the hunt for QAs for autonomous AI agents for a new project focused on validating and improving complex task structures, policy logic, and agent evaluation frameworks. Throughout the project, you'll have to balance quality assurance, research, and logical problem-solving. This project opportunity is ideal for people who enjoy looking at systems holistically and thinking through scenarios, implications, and edge cases.

You do not need a coding background, but you must be curious, intellectually rigorous, and capable of evaluating the soundness and consistency of complex setups. If you've ever excelled in things like consulting, CHGK, Olympiads, case solving, or systems thinking — you might be a great fit.

What you'll be doing:

- Reviewing evaluation tasks and scenarios for logic, completeness, and realism
- Identifying inconsistencies, missing assumptions, or unclear decision points
- Helping define clear expected behaviors (gold standards) for AI agents
- Annotating cause-effect relationships, reasoning paths, and plausible alternatives
- Thinking through complex systems and policies as a human would to ensure agents are tested properly
- Working closely with QA, writers, or developers to suggest refinements or edge case coverage

How to get started:

Apply to this post, qualify, and get the chance to contribute to a project aligned with your skills, on your own schedule. Shape the future of AI while building tools that benefit everyone.

Requirements

- Excellent analytical thinking: Can reason about complex systems, scenarios, and logical implications
- Strong attention to detail: Can spot contradictions, ambiguities, and vague requirements
- Familiarity with structured data formats: Can read, not necessarily write JSON/YAML
- Can assess scenarios holistically: What's missing, what's unrealistic, what might break?
- Good communication and clear writing (in English) to document your findings. 

We also value applicants who have:

- Experience with policy evaluation, logic puzzles, case studies, or structured scenario design
- Background in consulting, academia, olympiads (e.g. logic/math/informatics), or research
- Exposure to LLMs, prompt engineering, or AI-generated content
- Familiarity with QA or test-case thinking (edge cases, failure modes, "what could go wrong")
- Some understanding of how scoring or evaluation works in agent testing (precision, coverage, etc.)

Benefits

- Get paid for your expertise, with rates that can go up to $38/hour depending on your skills, experience, and project needs
- Take part in a flexible, remote, freelance project that fits around your primary professional or academic commitments
- Participate in an advanced AI project and gain valuable experience to enhance your portfolio
- Influence how future AI models understand and communicate in your field of expertise

Habitat Energy is a fast growing technology company focussed on the physical and financial optimisation of energy storage and renewable generation assets globally through complex models and trading. By maximising the returns from these assets we aim to drive investment in renewable energy and accelerate the transition to a low carbon world. Our rapidly growing team of 110+ people in Austin, TX, Oxford, UK, and Melbourne, Australia brings together exceptionally talented and passionate people in the domains of energy trading, data science, software engineering and renewable energy management.

We have a vacancy for a Business Analyst to join our team in Melbourne. This role is crucial to ensuring the requirements of our commercial teams, principally traders, are accurately captured, defined, and translated into actionable insights for our technical teams. Your work will directly influence the profitability and efficiency of our trading strategies by ensuring our technology is perfectly aligned with commercial needs. You will act as a collaborative partner, fostering seamless communication and alignment by bringing together the fast-paced world of energy trading and our software development lifecycle. Working closely with commercial and technical leads you’ll help to shape the product roadmap and ensure user stories are centrally tracked in a clear and concise fashion ready for development. This is a great fit for someone with experience in a business analysis or requirements engineering role who is comfortable in a highly dynamic commercial environment and skilled at translating complex user needs into technical specifications.

You’ll Play a Key Role In

- Bringing together our commercial trading team and our technical delivery teams.
- Leading requirements gathering sessions with traders and other commercial stakeholders to deeply understand their needs, workflows, and pain points.
- Translating commercial needs into clear, well-defined user stories, acceptance criteria, and functional specifications understood by the technology team.
- Contributing to the product roadmap, ensuring captured requirements align with business strategy and are effectively prioritised, with an opportunity to grow into a leadership role in this area.
- Supporting the agile delivery process by clarifying requirements, answering questions from the technical delivery team, encouraging communication and user involvement, and facilitating direct collaboration of tech & users throughout the build phase.
- Analysing and validating that the solutions developed meet the original business objectives and user requirements.
- Managing stakeholder expectations by ensuring clear and consistent communication between all parties.

You Will Be Responsible For

- Partnering with the commercial team to define and articulate their technology requirements.
- Creating and maintaining a clear and organised backlog of user & functional requirements, primarily through user stories in JIRA.
- Ensuring that business context and the "why" behind a requirement are clearly communicated across the commercial and technical delivery teams.
- Working closely with the commercial team to understand requirements originating from external customers.
- Facilitating workshops and interviews to elicit detailed requirements from users.
- Ensuring alignment between the commercial stakeholders and the technical delivery team on the scope and definition of a given feature or project.
- Promoting transparent communication across teams, ensuring that expectations, dependencies, and priorities are well understood.
- Providing updates to ensure transparency and alignment of requirements and outcomes within projects. 

Preferred Skills And Experience

- Proven experience as a Business Analyst, or in a similar role where you were responsible for gathering and defining user requirements for software development.
- Experience working closely with a commercial or business-focused team, such as traders, sales, or account managers.
- Expertise with agile development methodologies and workflow management tools, particularly JIRA.
- Experience with roadmapping tools like ProductBoard is highly advantageous.
- Exceptional communication, collaboration, and stakeholder management skills, with an ability to translate between technical and non-technical audiences.
- Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a talent for breaking down complex problems into manageable components.
- Self-motivated, detail-oriented, and able to work independently in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.
- Evidence of being able to successfully navigate competing priorities and manage the expectations of demanding stakeholders.
- A technical background or experience working directly with software development 

‘Nice To Have’ Skills And Experience

- Experience working in the energy, finance, or commodities trading sector.
- Business Analysis certifications.

Introduction:

About Us

Adelaide Primary Health Network (Adelaide PHN) is an independent, not for profit, primary health care organisation based in Adelaide. We aim to improve the health and wellbeing of the Adelaide community by coordinating and integrating health and community services and by working in partnership to identify local needs and create strategies in response to keeping people well and out of hospital; improving their experience AND their health outcomes - to deliver on our vision of ‘shaping the health system to deliver better outcomes for vulnerable people, and a healthier Adelaide’.

Why you should come work with us

Adelaide PHN offers a great range of benefits to our employees, including:

- Competitive remuneration and work-life balance.
- Access to generous not for profit salary packaging benefits, including up to $15,900 for living expenses and $2,650 for meal and entertainment.
- Additional paid leave between Christmas and New Year, in addition to annual leave entitlements.
- Three special leave days with pay each year that can be used for any purpose.
- Support for cultural diversity and employee wellbeing, including up to ten days of cultural leave per year. 
- Eight weeks of paid parental leave.
- Option to substitute public holidays.
- Generous allowance toward professional development.
- Family friendly and flexible working arrangements.
- Free Employment Assistance Program.

Description:

This Data Analyst role will have a key focus on supporting the data and reporting needs at the Adelaide PHN by:

- Proactively monitoring for new and emerging data to provide insights to health and service needs in the Adelaide PHN region and inform organisational strategic, operational and regulatory performance.
- Acting as a subject matter expert within the organisation regarding data and analytics as appropriate e.g. population health, aged care, mental health, methods/data collection systems
- Providing analysis, interpretation, and reporting/presentation of data to inform of a range of planning and performance deliverables, including, but not limited to, the Adelaide PHN Needs Assessment, 12-month performance report and annual report.
- Participating in data management and data governance.

The role may also undertake other data collection, analysis, reporting and quality improvement initiatives to support the wider organisation.

This position is offered as a full-time, 12 month fixed-term contract. Future employment is subject to ongoing funding.

There is flexibility to work from home 1-2 days per week post induction and training.

For more information, you can view the position description here (SEEK, Indeed and LinkedIn applicants please go to our website).

Skills and Experiences:

To be successful in this role you’ll need:

- Tertiary qualifications in data analytics, epidemiology, public health, evaluation, biostatistics or similar discipline, and/or significant relevant work experience in these fields is required. 
- Demonstrated experience working in primary health care and/or public health sectors. 
- Knowledge of the Australian primary health care sector, social determinants of health and population health data.
- Demonstrated experience undertaking analysis and developing reports to provide insights on organisational strategic, operational and regulatory performance.
- Proven ability to implement and manage appropriate systems and processes to maintain the quality and integrity of information and data (quantitative and qualitative).
- Demonstrated knowledge in research methodological skills and capacity to interpret findings including statistical analysis.
- High level critical thinking and analytic skills with exceptional attention to detail and accuracy.
- Demonstrated highly competent computer skills and use of computer programs for data management and analysis, particularly Power BI and/or other reporting tools and business intelligence solutions.
- Demonstrated effective written and verbal communication skills, with a focus on facilitating and maintaining relationships. 
- Demonstrated ability to work autonomously and in teams, including across internal portfolios and external groups, in a collaborative environment.

You may have experience in previous roles in the primary or public health sector such as: Health Data Analyst, Business Intelligence Analyst or Officer, Health Research Analyst or Officer, Health Reporting Analyst, Population Health Analyst or Officer.

If so, we would love to hear from you!

How To Apply

Only individuals with significant health sector experience need apply.

Apply now by clicking on Apply and include a maximum 2 page cover letter outlining your suitability for the role along with your resume.

Applications will ONLY be considered when received through our careers portal.

To apply, you must have the legal right to work in Australia and your employment will be subject to an acceptable National Police Check.

Shortlisting for this position will commence immediately and we reserve our right to close this position at any time if a suitable candidate is found.

For further information about this role, please contact Donna Shotton, Planning and Performance Manager, on 08 8219 5900 (Monday - Thursday). Please do not attempt to contact direct via email or LinkedIn.

All enquiries and applications will be handled professionally and with the strictest of confidence.

About The Role

We are excited to share an opportunity for the role of ESG Analyst to join Vinarchy’s Global Safety & Sustainability team. This is a full time, permanent position based in Adelaide and offering hybrid working.

The ESG Analyst will play a key role in supporting the global sustainability & climate strategy by managing data, analytics, and reporting across environmental, social, and governance (ESG) areas.

You’ll support the Global Sustainability & Climate Transition Manager in delivering robust ESG disclosures, tracking performance against targets (e.g. emissions, water, waste), and ensuring alignment with global frameworks such as TCFD, SBTi, GRI, and CSRD.

Communications skills will be key as you work closely with teams across global regions to provide insights that drive progress toward Vinarchy’s climate and sustainability goals.

Key Responsibilities

- Collect, validate, and manage ESG performance data across global operations, ensuring accuracy and audit readiness. 
- Support the implementation and optimisation of ESG data platforms and tools (e.g., Intelex). 
- Develop dashboards and visualisations to communicate sustainability performance effectively. 
- Assist in preparing ESG disclosures aligned with frameworks such as TCFD, GRI, SASB, CDP, and SBTi. 
- Contribute to Vinarchy’s annual Sustainability Report and other stakeholder publications. 
- Track global ESG reporting obligations and coordinate submissions to rating agencies and investor questionnaires. 
- Support ESG software rollout, user onboarding, training, and ongoing system improvements. 
- Analyse environmental metrics including Scope 1–3 emissions, energy, water, and waste, and support climate risk assessments. 
- Provide analytical support for sustainability initiatives such as renewable energy, biodiversity, and packaging. 
- Research ESG trends and best practices to drive continuous improvement and enhance internal capabilities. 

Other Requirements

- Occasional travel may be required to operational sites or regional offices 
- Role may expand as ESG frameworks and regulations evol

What We're Looking For

- Tertiary qualification in Environmental Science, Sustainability, Data Analytics, Finance, or a related discipline 
- 2–4 years' experience in ESG, sustainability analytics, corporate reporting, or data governance 
- Familiarity with key ESG reporting frameworks (e.g., GHG Protocol, CDP, GRI, TCFD) 
- Advanced Excel/data analysis skills, with proficiency in Power BI, Tableau, or similar tools 
- Strong attention to detail and organisational skills

Dogs, cats, budgies and everything in between - pets deserve the world. They make us want to be better humans. That’s why we’ve made it our mission to build the most engaged and passionate community of pets and pet parents across the world. And we’re looking for talented team mates who can help us do it.

Founded in Sydney, our team of 500+ pet obsessives span Australia, New Zealand and the Philippines. We’ve scaled to become one of Australia's top five eComm companies and the no.1 online pet store. But we’re just getting started. Like a whippet who’s spotted their mate across the dog park, our growth is only going to accelerate, as we continue to disrupt the way that pet parents shop.

Excitingly, the pet industry is booming (as in $15 billion kind of booming) and online pet retail is set to grow exponentially in the next five years. So this is a unique career opportunity to be part of our epic growth story.

The opportunity

Data Analysts at Pet Circle are problem-solvers who provide rapid, reliable insights that drive data-informed decisions across the business. Working exclusively within our governed business data environment, you'll use tools like BigQuery and Looker to deliver high-quality dashboards and fast answers to business questions.

At Pet Circle, we’ve built a governed, user-friendly data environment that allows Analysts to do what they do best - explore, analyse, and generate insights. You’ll be able to focus on answering business questions and uncovering opportunities, with the support of a strong engineering and data science team behind you.

This role is a 12 month FTC. There is potential for a permanent opportunity.

What You’ll Be Doing

- Using our Business Data Layer – Writing SQL queries against curated, governed datasets for consistent and trusted outputs.
- Writing and executing SQL in BigQuery Console – Running ad hoc queries quickly, using the web console (no IDEs or terminals).
- Leveraging Looker Explores – Knowing when and how to use each Explore effectively.
- Building insightful dashboards – Creating compelling, easy-to-use dashboards in Looker, using existing data without LookML development.
- Answering business questions – Providing timely, accurate responses to ad hoc data requests.
- Performing deeper analytics – Exploring drivers of trends and delivering actionable insights beyond dashboards.

Tools you’ll use

-  BigQuery Console - ad hoc SQL queries
-  Looker - data exploration and dashboards
-  Looker Studio - lightweight reporting

The ideal toolbox

- Advanced SQL: Write performant, accurate queries and self-validate outputs.
-  Looker (advanced user): Build dashboards, apply visual design best practice, debug performance issues.
-  Looker Studio: Build lightweight, interactive reports.
-  Basic LookML literacy: Understand structures and make safe model changes via Jenny automation (e.g. adding columns).
- Self-aware: Recognises limitations and knows when to seek help.
- Confident in core skills: Operates independently with SQL and Looker.
- Data curious: Always asks “why?” and explores trends in depth.
- Business-oriented: Produces insights that are timely, relevant, and actionable.

Role location

We believe that building connections and collaborating as Pet Circlers is super important. So this role is based in Sydney with a hybrid arrangement of 3 days per week in our pet friendly offices (your pet might love coming to the office even more than you). This is subject to change in line with business requirements.

Juicy perks

- Heaps of development opportunities - stretch projects, secondments and unlimited learning courses via Go1
- Flexible working environment
- Up to 50% employee discount
- Product sample giveaways
- Pawrental leave and wellbeing leave
- Team charity volunteer days
- Classpass subsidy

Why Join?

We Reckon Our Mission To Help The World Pet Better Is An Important One, But Also An Incredibly Fun And Rewarding One. Becoming a Pet Circler Means You’re Committed To Help Shape An Entire Industry - It’s Pretty Exciting Stuff. Here’s What We Stand For

- We're better together
- We operate with humble hearts and hungry minds
- Pets matter' so pets and pet parents always have a seat at our table
- We're instinctively curious. Always.

Belong at Pet Circle

Our unique perspectives and expertise is our superpower - we value diversity in all forms. So, no matter your background, please apply if this role makes you excited to bring your full self to work each day.

The CMG Analyst is responsible for assisting clients in accessing global debt markets across both bonds and loans products and is also responsible for the support of the senior originators in the CMG Sydney team

Capital Markets Mandate

- Develop a sustainable, client focused, flow oriented, primary markets origination business for MUFG clients in Oceania
- Develop value-added direct CMG client relationships with bond and loan issuer clients across Oceania.
- Work with relationship managers to develop/broaden the overall relationship with core clients by providing high quality support and product interface with regard to capital markets financing opportunities
- Origination of debt transactions for issuance into global capital markets

Your role in contributing to this mandate will be (where applicable):

- Deliver and grow a sustainable, client-focused, flow-oriented, primary and secondary business.
- Maximise profitability from leveraging and enhancing the Group’s customer franchise.
- Work in partnership with Sales, Trading and Research in MUFG to deliver products that meet the needs of our clients
- Collaborate with the relevant teams in other Group entities to advance the business globally.
- In all activities, protect and enhance the firm’s, and the Group’s, reputation. Working in partnership with other parts of the Group to deliver franchise and business growth.
- Expand the size and diversity of the client-base
- Conduct business in line with regulatory requirements (including Volcker, EMIR and MIFID).

Responsibilities include:

- Preparing high-quality pitchbooks and materials for client meetings and follow-ups
- Provide regular market and pricing updates for internal and external clients
- Perform analytical work for client funding or corporate requirements
- Proactively create trade ideas and new business proposals which meet our client’s needs
- React to client enquiries in a risk-sensitive manner, ensuring proposed solutions are appropriate for the client and meet the requirements of best execution.
- Engage and build relationship with client working level teams to ensure smooth execution
- Supporting team CMG deal lead in internal approvals process
- Ensure AML/KYC and compliance standards are met for all transactions
- Coordinate between all internal and external stakeholders and deal team members to ensure smooth execution from mandate to deal closing
- Deal execution aspects includes due diligence, structuring, documentation, ratings, investor marketing, roadshow planning, settlement, post-mortems
- Internal Reporting requirements (team lead working with CMG and local Planning teams)

Requirements

- 1 - 3 years work experience (experience in financial markets will be viewed upon favourably)
- Analytical background with strong attention to detail
- Resourceful and ‘can-do’ attitude with ability to work well with internal and external parties
- Good grasp of excel, word and powerpoint

Do you have a desire to make a positive impact on the climate and biodiversity crises by working with an innovative global think tank? If so, we want to hear from you!

InfluenceMap is best known for its LobbyMap platform, which analyzes corporate advocacy and policy engagement activities related to climate change and biodiversity loss. Our work has been featured in the media globally, used by hundreds of investors, and informed numerous climate campaigns. Other work streams include the FinanceMap platform, which assesses the climate credentials of the financial sector, and the Carbon Majors platform, which tracks emissions from the world's largest polluters. With offices in London, New York, Tokyo, Seoul, Canberra, and Brussels, this is an opportunity to be part of a team of 70+ friendly and dynamic professionals and to help shape our culture as we continue to grow and evolve as an organization. You will also have the chance to work with our global network of partners to help develop and share our cutting-edge content.

We are seeking an Analyst to join our team who will be responsible for assessing companies on their climate change and/or biodiversity loss policies. This is an entry-level analyst position that is likely to suit someone starting their career. You will be working on the LobbyMap workstream. By mastering our methodology and processes, you will have the opportunity to specialize in corporate climate policy engagement in China.

Full training in our research methods and how to effectively communicate our results will be provided. Upon demonstrating your ability in this specialization, you may also have the opportunity to develop expertise in other areas, such as specific sectors, policy areas, or geographic regions, in line with the organization's project needs. Our approach is highly data-driven and emphasizes accuracy, consistency, and meticulous attention to detail. InfluenceMap's work is in widespread use by finance, the media, and other stakeholders; thus, we place great importance on the ability to communicate our content (both written and verbal) effectively.

Requirements

To be successful in this role at InfluenceMap, you should have:

- Native Chinese reading, writing, and speaking skills (Simplified Chinese essential, Traditional Chinese preferred)
- Fluency in English (written and spoken) 
- Outstanding analytical and data analysis skills, with a very strong attention to detail 
- Ability to communicate complex issues and data-driven analysis convincingly
- IT and software skills across a range of standard applications
- Right to work in Japan or Australia. 

We are an enthusiastic, highly motivated, mission-aligned team. We are seeking a candidate with a similar outlook.

Benefits

Details of Benefits:

- This is a full-time position
- Location: This position could be based in Japan or Australia. We have offices in Tokyo and Canberra, where flexible and hybrid working arrangements are possible.
- Competitive salary 
- Generous annual leave package 
- Extra three paid days, organization-wide closure at the end of the calendar year
- InfluenceMap provides all statutory benefits as part of its employment package.
- Frequent interactions with a dynamic and global, mission-driven team!

Our people are customer obsessed. They prioritise the needs and satisfaction of the customer above all else. Our mindset fosters innovation and creates strong, lasting customer relationships as we strive to be the most customer centric company in Australia and New Zealand.

In the role of Fraud Assist Analyst, you will be answering critical calls from our customers that may have been impacted by fraud.

This role is a 12 month fixed term contract starting November 2025.

 Each day, you’ll go above and beyond to: 

- Make sure our customers feel safe and informed by giving them the right information about our process and products.  
- Receiving up to 40 inbound calls a day from customers who have been impacted by fraud and require support.

Brief Description

Purpose of the Role:

As our new Fraud Performance Analyst, you will play a key role in protecting our business and customers by monitoring fraud trends, assessing control effectiveness and driving improvements in fraud detection strategies. Alongside a strong analytical and reporting focus, the Fraud Performance Analyst will work closely with the Fraud function to optimise and scale detection methodologies, reporting and controls.

You Will

- Develop & continuously monitor the performance of new and existing rules-based typologies and detection models to support fraud detection objectives 
- Proactively provide timely and data driven analysis and insights to better support and inform business understanding and decisions and provide recommendations of corrective actions to address business challenges 
- In conjunction with Data & Analytics teams, produce and monitor performance and operational reporting to inform decision making
- Ensure typology analysis supports compliance with relevant legislation and regulatory expectations (GICOP) 
- Support the team in pursuing and developing new business initiatives, including defining, modelling and tracking of business case benefits and identify & provide insight into drivers of cost, productivity, trends and claims leakage 
- Support the Leadership team to define and track initiative benefits aligned with the strategic direction 
- Promote and contribute to an environment of continuous improvement and innovative thinking while encouraging initiatives and creativity in detecting and embedding fraud detection methodologies

Knowledge And Experience

- Strong data analysis skills including SQL, Excel, Power BI, along with the ability to interpret complex data, identify patterns & clearly communicate insights
- An understanding of fraud typologies, advantageous 
- 2 years’ experience in business or fraud performance analysis, and a working knowledge of Claims Insurance business and processes 
- Demonstrated collaborative and consultative approach to work, with the ability to work both independently as well as within a small team 
- Accuracy driven, with high attention to detail and the ability to multitask in a fast-paced/ dynamic environment, with the ability to work proactively, autonomously and meet tight deadlines

- Take care of yourself - your wellbeing is important to us and our healthy mind and body hub, mental-health support and fitness discounts will help you be your best self. 
- Celebrate the wins - we love sharing our successes and celebrating together - join us and you’ve got a ticket to our many on-site events throughout the year, family fun days and annual celebrations. 
- Access to A&G’s employee reward and recognition platform, powered by Rewards Gateway - Enjoy a wide range of benefits, including personalised rewards & peer-to-peer recognition, exclusive discounts & savings across more than 600 top retailers and a comprehensive recognition program that celebrates milestones and achievements - helping you feel valued every step of the way.

Position Accountabilities

- Develop and continuously monitor the performance of new and existing rules based typologies and detection models to support fraud detection objectives
- Proactively provide timely and data driven analysis and insights to better support and inform business understanding and decisions and provide recommendations of corrective actions to address business challenges
